docs.abstract: A consumer group says insurers sometimes charge more to people living in less affluent ZIP codes — even if they have good driving records.
docs.snippet: A consumer group says insurers sometimes charge more to people living in less affluent ZIP codes — even if they have good driving records.
docs.lead_paragraph: Living in the wrong ZIP code — even a short distance from a boundary — may mean a difference of hundreds of dollars in your automobile insurance rates, a new analysis finds.

headline.main: Your Neighbor in an Adjacent ZIP Code May Pay Less for Car Insurance
headline.print_headline: Car Insurance Rates Go Up  On ‘Wrong Side’ of ZIP Codes

docs.abstract: The North Lawndale headquarters, a source of pride to residents before the retailer moved downtown, has slowly been redeveloped after years of sitting vacant.
docs.snippet: The North Lawndale headquarters, a source of pride to residents before the retailer moved downtown, has slowly been redeveloped after years of sitting vacant.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Sears filed for bankruptcy last fall, many Chicagoans found themselves reminiscing about its glory days, particularly in North Lawndale, on the city’s West Side, where the retailer’s original headquarters still stand.

headline.main: Former Sears Complex Returns as a Beacon in a Chicago Neighborhood
headline.print_headline: Long After Sears Left, Its Buildings Thrive Again

docs.abstract: Changing the role of shareholders is only a start. Boards and C.E.O.s must create more higher-paying jobs.
docs.snippet: Changing the role of shareholders is only a start. Boards and C.E.O.s must create more higher-paying jobs.
docs.lead_paragraph: American businesses are sending a clear message: They need to focus on doing more than making profit. On Monday, the Business Roundtable, which represents the largest corporations in the United States, published a new, broader statement about the purpose of business, declaring that delivering shareholder value is not enough. The United States Chamber of Commerce, which represents three million businesses, revised its purpose last year to focus on job creation.

headline.main: Save Capitalism by Paying People More
